<p>The distinctive smells of spearmint and of caraway seeds are produced by mirror images of the same molecule, carvone.</p>
<p>The fact that we can distinguish these smells shows that our olfactory receptors can sometimes discern the &#8220;handedness&#8221; of such molecules. But this isn&#8217;t the case with every set of &#8220;enantiomers.&#8221;</p>
